had long ben settled in Sussex.  很久以前就定居在苏塞克斯。

Their estate was large, and their residence was at Norland Park, 
in the centre of their property, where, for many generations(生活了很多代人), 
they had lived in so respectable a manner as to engage the general good opinion of their surrounding acquaintance.

The late owner of this estate was a single man, who lived to a very advanced age, and who for many years of his life, 两个who引导的定语从句
had a constant companion and housekeeper in his sister.有一个长期的陪伴和管理家务的角色在他妹妹身上。

 But her death, which happened ten years before his own, produced a great alteration in his home; 
for to supply her loss, he invited and received into his house the family of his nephew Mr. Henry Dashwood, 
the legal inheritor of the Norland estate, and the person to whom he intended to bequeath（遗赠） it.

In the society of his nephew and niece, and their children, the old Gentleman's days were comfortably spent。（他的日子很舒服地消耗）

His attachment(附件，依恋) to them all increased

The constant attention of Mr. and Mrs. Henry Dashwood to his wishes, which proceeded not merely from interest, but from goodness of heart, 
gave him every degree of solid comfort which his age could receive; 
and the cheerfulness of the children added a relish to his existence.









  
